&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Senior Accountant at Nature’s Bakery, you’ll play a key role in ensuring accurate financial reporting, maintaining compliance with US GAAP, and supporting month-end close and internal control processes. You bring strong technical accounting expertise, excellent analytical skills, and experience with ERP systems and other accounting software tools. You thrive in a fast-paced environment, communicate effectively with team members at all levels, and have the flexibility to adapt to shifting priorities. Most importantly, you’re passionate about driving process improvements and creating efficiencies that make a real impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and review journal entries, account reconciliations, monthly close processes, settling monthly intercompany receivables &amp;amp; payables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record acquisitions, transfers, disposals, and depreciation of fixed assets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform complex and bank and account reconciliations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with US GAAP, internal controls, and accounting policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee Concur review and approvals, monthly billing &amp;amp; accruals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and enhance accounting systems, processes, and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support internal and external audits: ensure ongoing compliance with company policies and regulatory standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with policies related to ethics, confidentiality, and safety&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform additional accounting tasks and special projects as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure accuracy and consistency in financial reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify process improvement opportunities within accounting workflows and systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 – 7+ years of progressive accounting experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical knowledge of US GAAP Hands-on experience with S4Hana, Concur &amp;amp; OneStream preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Microsoft Office Suite – Excel (formulas, Pivot tables, PowerQueries), Word &amp;amp; PowerPoint&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Power BI preferred Proven ability to manage multiple priorities in a fast-paced environment Excellent analytical, organizational, and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills and a collaborative mindset Ability to interface with different levels of the workforce&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Microsoft Office Excel, Word &amp;amp; PowerPoint is required&lt;/li&gt;
