&lt;p&gt;As a Receiving Coordinator, you are an essential worker, responsible for processing inbound goods. They are tasked with receiving all factory materials, verifying the quantities delivered, and recording goods receipts in our inventory management system. They ensure that the materials received match the delivery paperwork and meet our high material quality standards. The Receiving Coordinator is responsible for working closely with the purchasing department to schedule deliveries effectively, promoting smooth product flow. The coordinator ensures all applicable records are completed, filed, and audit-ready.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Shipping Coordinator, you are responsible for ensuring outbound product is properly staged, accounted for, loaded, and goods-issued against the correct order. They will also inspect all arriving trailers to ensure they meet our strict quality standards for shipping our products. The shipping coordinator is responsible for maintaining all outbound paperwork and prepared for audit inspection at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
